**4.2 Dependency Map**
React UI -> (HTTP/WebSockets) -> FastAPI Backend -> (Admin SDK) -> Firebase Firestore.
React UI -> (Client SDK) -> Firebase Auth.

**4.3 Most fragile part of stack?**
The WebSocket connection state management. Dropped connections on mobile networks require robust client-side reconnection logic (`useWebSocket` hook handles basic retries, but complex state desync can occur under poor cellular conditions).

**4.4 Best decision made?**
Separating the frontend and backend entirely and using FastAPI. It allows the Python backend to focus heavily on complex simulation/AI logic (where Python excels) while React handles entirely separate UI state.


